  "title": "Assistant Engineer / Service Engineer (Electrical/Mechanical/Marine)",
  "description": "<ul><li><p>Location: East / West / North (Across Singapore)</p></li><li><p>5 days work week</p></li><li><p>Basic $2000 - $3500 (Based on experience)</p></li><li><p>OT pay entitled</p></li><li></li></ul><h2>Assistant Engineer / Service Engineer / Service Technician (Mechanical /Electrical/Marine)</h2><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Assist in engineering design, installation, testing, or maintenance works</p></li><li><p>Prepare technical drawings, reports, and documentation</p></li><li><p>Support senior engineers and project teams</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with vendors and contractors</p></li><li><p>Perform troubleshooting and basic site supervision</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Perform installation, servicing, troubleshooting, and maintenance</p></li><li><p>Attend on-site service calls and inspections</p></li><li><p>Prepare service reports and documentation</p></li><li><p>Liaise with customers on technical issues</p></li><li><p>Support commissioning and testing activities</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma / NITEC in Engineering or technical discipline</p></li><li><p>Entry-level candidates welcome as training will be provided</p></li><li><p>Experience in servicing industrial or mechanical equipment preferred</p></li><li><p>Willing to travel and work on-site</p></li><li><p>Class 3 driving license is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Willing to learn and hands-on</p></li><li></li></ul><p>To Apply, kindly click on the \"APPLY NOW\" button.</p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>StaffKing Pte Ltd (20C0358) | Chong Kar Ming (John) (R21101412)</p>",
